The SIU will investigate the Mopani District Municipality in Limpopo Harry Gwala District Municipality in KwaZulu-Natal as well as of the Provincial Department of Agriculture and Rural Development and Mjindi Farming in KwaZulu-Natal.All three SIUs according to the Presidency will look into alleged improper and unlawful conduct by councillors officials or employees of the municipalities and department.They will also look at unlawful expenditure of public money irregular and unapproved acquisitive act intentional or negligent loss of public money or damage to public property as well as improper conduct by any person which has caused or may cause serious harm to the interests of the public.The proclamations do not state why the investigations are required.